<br>
Personally I don't care for the proposed change or consider the ability to charm a level 60+ mob overpowered.  After all, if you're going to drudge up the fact that mobs do more damage now, then don't forget to include the fact that all classes do more damage as well and have infinitely more hit points than they did in previous expansions.  But I suspect the change has more to do with the fact that Verant didn't take into account the possibility that charmed mobs would be used extensively in these &quot;high end&quot; encounters.  But I doubt that even an NPC with a 1% slow effect will suddenly not outdamage rogues and monks.<br>
